imized for modern systems for most platforms, and the limited way that lighttpd uses libev does not provide any advantages over the os-specific optimized event handlers.  x-ref:   \"fd leak with libev in 1.4.42\"   https://redmine.lighttpd.net/issues/2761','fdevent_libev.c','125','29','5','2','true','false','false','2016-10-29 09:13:49-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','23503883babccc578ddde4a5b9a4a6d2cd020320','Glenn Strauss','[core] fix potential streaming tempfile corruption (fixes #2760)  set o_append after mkstemp() in chunk.c  (mkostemp() is not as portable) (also set fd_cloexec to avoid potentially leaking open tempfiles to cgi)  (thx dieter.ro for helping track this down)  x-ref:   https://redmine.lighttpd.net/boards/3/topics/6884   \"potential tempfile corruption when streaming response\"   https://redmine.lighttpd.net/issues/2760','chunk.c','522','134','3','0','true','false','false','2016-10-29 09:14:07-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','204df0681400da072116633b1d4368e6aa900d13','Glenn Strauss','minor: coverity comments','chunk.c','522','134','1','0','false','false','false','2016-10-29 09:14:07-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','204df0681400da072116633b1d4368e6aa900d13','Glenn Strauss','minor: coverity comments','mod_authn_gssapi.c','580','118','2','1','false','false','false','2016-10-29 09:14:07-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','b29e69e5b746d1ee1d371893170b6ce31bbdb20e','Glenn Strauss','[mod_scgi] fix prefix matching to always match url  fix mod_scgi prefix matching: match the prefix always against url, not the absolute filepath (regardless of check-local)  (apply fix similar to commit:fe8b7e57 applied to mod_fastcgi in 2008)','mod_scgi.c','1965','464','8','7','true','false','false','2016-10-29 09:14:07-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','cd48c2804b2d38945c25e12d5253eb2f4edcce29','Glenn Strauss','move script to doc/scripts/ax_prog_cc_for_build.m4  m4/ directory is listed in .gitignore and should be generated','autogen.sh','11','0','1','0','false','false','false','2016-10-29 09:51